parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, tachometer, and other gauges to malfunction or fail, leading to a safety issue as the driver is unable to accurately monitor the vehicle's speed and performance.
symptoms: The speedometer and tachometer needles move erratically or stick
the gauges give false readings
the instrument panel lights dim or fail
and the warning lights on the dashboard illuminate incorrectly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: The headlights turn off intermittently
the low-beam lights fail to function
and the high-beam lights malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including the failure of critical systems such as the headlights, instrument cluster, and anti-theft device.
symptoms: The electrical system malfunctions
causing the headlights
instrument cluster
and anti-theft device to fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank inlet fracture can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and serious injuries. It can also cause the check engine light to illuminate, and the vehicle may shake abnormally while driving.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel odors inside and outside the vehicle
check engine light illumination
abnormal vehicle shaking
inability to fill the tank to capacity
fuel leaks on inclines or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Inlet Check Valve Fracture and Leaking Seals
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the fuel tank inlet check valve and leaking seals can cause fuel to leak, leading to a potential fire hazard, and the smell of fuel in the cabin area, which can be hazardous to the driver's health.
symptoms: Strong smell of fuel inside and outside the vehicle
fuel leaking from the tank
engine light comes on
crack at the opening of the gas tank.
